%N A368497 Decimal expansion of the solution to x = Sum_{k>=1} (prime(k) - x) / Product_{i=1..k-1} prime(i).
%C A368497 The sum part S(x) = Sum_{k>=1} (prime(k) - x) / Product_{i=1..k-1} prime(i) ranges between for instance S(3/2) = A341930 = 2.067... and S(2) = A340469 = 1.214... and the present constant is where S(x) = x.
%C A368497 With this constant as h(1) = x, sequence h(n+1) = ceiling(h(n)) * (h(n) - ceiling(h(n)) + x) is real numbers with the property that ceiling(h(n)) = prime(n).
